      "content": "i get that it was based on stereotypes, but for the sake of the debate, i need to be able to present the \"pro-policy\" side without it sounding like just a collection of slurs or obvious hate. \n\ncould you help me frame those arguments in more \"academic\" or \"socio-economic\" terms that a policymaker from that era might have actually used? like, instead of just saying \"it's because of race,\" how would they argue that maintaining demographic homogeneity was actually a pragmatic strategy for long-term urban planning or social cohesion? i need the most sophisticated version of that argument to make the debate realistic.",
